==== ENTRY 1 ====
HEADWORD: Sitfast
<hw>Sit"fast`</hw> <pr>(?)</pr>, <pos>a.</pos> <ety>[<ets>Sit</ets> +
<ets>fast</ets>.]</ety> <def>Fixed; stationary; immovable.</def>
<mark>[R.]</mark>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

<p><q>'T is good, when you have crossed the sea and back,⟦br⟧
To find the <qex>sitfast</qex> acres where you left them.</q>
<rj><qau>Emerson.</qau></rj>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

<p><ent>Sitfast</ent>⟦br⟧

==== ENTRY 2 ====
HEADWORD: Sitfast
<hw>Sit"fast`</hw>, <pos>n.</pos> <fld>(Far.)</fld> <def>A callosity
with inflamed edges, on the back of a horse, under the saddle.</def>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

<p><ent>Sith</ent>⟦br⟧
